#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:5
msgid "NumPy 2.2.0 Release Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:7
msgid ""
"The NumPy 2.2.0 release is quick release that brings us back into sync with "
"the usual twice yearly release cycle. There have been an number of small "
"cleanups, as well as work bringing the new StringDType to completion and "
"improving support for free threaded Python. Highlights are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:12
msgid "New functions ``matvec`` and ``vecmat``, see below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:13
msgid "Many improved annotations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:14
msgid "Improved support for the new StringDType."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:15
msgid "Improved support for free threaded Python"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:16
msgid "Fixes for f2py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:18
msgid "This release supports Python versions 3.10-3.13."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:22
msgid "Deprecations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:24
msgid ""
"``_add_newdoc_ufunc`` is now deprecated. ``ufunc.__doc__ = newdoc`` should "
"be used instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:27 ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:85
msgid "(`gh-27735 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27735>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:31
msgid "Expired deprecations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:33
msgid ""
"``bool(np.array([]))`` and other empty arrays will now raise an error. Use "
"``arr.size > 0`` instead to check whether an array has no elements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:36
msgid "(`gh-27160 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27160>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:40
msgid "Compatibility notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:42
msgid ""
"`numpy.cov` now properly transposes single-row (2d array) design matrices "
"when ``rowvar=False``. Previously, single-row design matrices would return a "
"scalar in this scenario, which is not correct, so this is a behavior change "
"and an array of the appropriate shape will now be returned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:47
msgid "(`gh-27661 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27661>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:51
msgid "New Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:53
msgid "New functions for matrix-vector and vector-matrix products"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:55
msgid "Two new generalized ufuncs were defined:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:57
msgid ""
"`numpy.matvec` - matrix-vector product, treating the arguments as stacks of "
"matrices and column vectors, respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:60
msgid ""
"`numpy.vecmat` - vector-matrix product, treating the arguments as stacks of "
"column vectors and matrices, respectively. For complex vectors, the "
"conjugate is taken."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:64
msgid ""
"These add to the existing `numpy.matmul` as well as to `numpy.vecdot`, which "
"was added in numpy 2.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:67
msgid ""
"Note that `numpy.matmul` never takes a complex conjugate, also not when its "
"left input is a vector, while both `numpy.vecdot` and `numpy.vecmat` do take "
"the conjugate for complex vectors on the left-hand side (which are taken to "
"be the ones that are transposed, following the physics convention)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:73
msgid "(`gh-25675 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/25675>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:75
msgid ""
"``np.complexfloating[T, T]`` can now also be written as ``np."
"complexfloating[T]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:78
msgid "(`gh-27420 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27420>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:80
msgid ""
"UFuncs now support ``__dict__`` attribute and allow overriding ``__doc__`` "
"(either directly or via ``ufunc.__dict__[\"__doc__\"]``). ``__dict__`` can "
"be used to also override other properties, such as ``__module__`` or "
"``__qualname__``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:87
msgid ""
"The \"nbit\" type parameter of ``np.number`` and its subtypes now defaults "
"to ``typing.Any``. This way, type-checkers will infer annotations such as "
"``x: np.floating``  as ``x: np.floating[Any]``, even in strict mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:91
msgid "(`gh-27736 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27736>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:95
msgid "Improvements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:97
msgid ""
"The ``datetime64`` and ``timedelta64`` hashes now correctly match the "
"Pythons builtin ``datetime`` and ``timedelta`` ones.  The hashes now "
"evaluated equal even for equal values with different time units."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:101
msgid "(`gh-14622 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/14622>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:103
msgid ""
"Fixed a number of issues around promotion for string ufuncs with StringDType "
"arguments. Mixing StringDType and the fixed-width DTypes using the string "
"ufuncs should now generate much more uniform results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:107
msgid "(`gh-27636 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27636>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:109
msgid ""
"Improved support for empty `memmap`. Previously an empty `memmap` would fail "
"unless a non-zero ``offset`` was set. Now a zero-size `memmap` is supported "
"even if ``offset=0``. To achieve this, if a `memmap` is mapped to an empty "
"file that file is padded with a single byte."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:114
msgid "(`gh-27723 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27723>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:117
msgid "``f2py`` handles multiple modules and exposes variables again"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:118
msgid ""
"A regression has been fixed which allows F2PY users to expose variables to "
"Python in modules with only assignments, and also fixes situations where "
"multiple modules are present within a single source file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:122
msgid "(`gh-27695 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27695>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:126
msgid "Performance improvements and changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:128
msgid ""
"Improved multithreaded scaling on the free-threaded build when many threads "
"simultaneously call the same ufunc operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:131
msgid "(`gh-27896 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27896>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:133
msgid ""
"NumPy now uses fast-on-failure attribute lookups for protocols.  This can "
"greatly reduce overheads of function calls or array creation especially with "
"custom Python objects.  The largest improvements will be seen on Python 3.12 "
"or newer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:138
msgid "(`gh-27119 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27119>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:140
msgid ""
"OpenBLAS on x86_64 and i686 is built with fewer kernels. Based on "
"benchmarking, there are 5 clusters of performance around these kernels: "
"``PRESCOTT NEHALEM SANDYBRIDGE HASWELL SKYLAKEX``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:144
msgid "OpenBLAS on windows is linked without quadmath, simplifying licensing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:146
msgid ""
"Due to a regression in OpenBLAS on windows, the performance improvements "
"when using multiple threads for OpenBLAS 0.3.26 were reverted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:149
msgid "(`gh-27147 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27147>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:151
msgid ""
"NumPy now indicates hugepages also for large ``np.zeros`` allocations on "
"linux.  Thus should generally improve performance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:154
msgid "(`gh-27808 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27808>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:158
msgid "Changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:160
msgid ""
"`numpy.fix` now won't perform casting to a floating data-type for integer "
"and boolean data-type input arrays."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:163
msgid "(`gh-26766 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/26766>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:165
msgid ""
"The type annotations of ``numpy.float64`` and ``numpy.complex128`` now "
"reflect that they are also subtypes of the built-in ``float`` and "
"``complex`` types, respectively. This update prevents static type-checkers "
"from reporting errors in cases such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:170
msgid ""
"x: float = numpy.float64(6.28)  # valid\n"
"z: complex = numpy.complex128(-1j)  # valid"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:175
msgid "(`gh-27334 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27334>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:177
msgid ""
"The ``repr`` of arrays large enough to be summarized (i.e., where elements "
"are replaced with ``...``) now includes the ``shape`` of the array, similar "
"to what already was the case for arrays with zero size and non-obvious "
"shape. With this change, the shape is always given when it cannot be "
"inferred from the values.  Note that while written as ``shape=...``, this "
"argument cannot actually be passed in to the ``np.array`` constructor. If "
"you encounter problems, e.g., due to failing doctests, you can use the print "
"option ``legacy=2.1`` to get the old behaviour."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:186
msgid "(`gh-27482 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27482>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:188
msgid ""
"Calling ``__array_wrap__`` directly on NumPy arrays or scalars now does the "
"right thing when ``return_scalar`` is passed (Added in NumPy 2).  It is "
"further safe now to call the scalar ``__array_wrap__`` on a non-scalar "
"result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:193
msgid "(`gh-27807 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27807>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:195
msgid ""
"Bump the musllinux CI image and wheels to 1_2 from 1_1. This is because 1_1 "
"is `end of life <https://github.com/pypa/manylinux/issues/1629>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:198
msgid "(`gh-27088 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27088>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:201
msgid "NEP 50 promotion state option removed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:202
msgid ""
"The NEP 50 promotion state settings are now removed. They were always meant "
"as temporary means for testing.  A warning will be given if the environment "
"variable is set to anything but ``NPY_PROMOTION_STATE=weak`` while "
"``_set_promotion_state`` and ``_get_promotion_state`` are removed.  In case "
"code used ``_no_nep50_warning``, a ``contextlib.nullcontext`` could be used "
"to replace it when not available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.2.0-notes.rst:209
msgid "(`gh-27156 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/27156>`__)"
msgstr ""
